CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1772132672
OL,3,CUniversity not told of psychiatrist's
OL,4,Cconcerns that Valdo Calocane might kill
OL,6,FIn evidence to the inquiry on
OL,7,FWednesday, Claire Thompson, the former
OL,8,Fassociate director of student
OL,9,Fwellbeing at the University of
OL,10,FNottingham, said Calocane studied
OL,11,Fthere from September 2017 to July 2022.
OL,13,FThe inquiry was told Calocane, who was
OL,14,F31 at the time of the attacks, was
OL,15,Fadmitted to a mental health ward in
OL,16,F2020 due to a psychotic episode in May
OL,17,F2020.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1772132672
OL,3,CUniversity not told of psychiatrist's
OL,4,Cconcerns that Valdo Calocane might kill
OL,6,FFollowing a message to the university
OL,7,Fsent by Calocane's mother in June
OL,8,F2020, a university case summary email
OL,9,Fnoted that he had been admitted under
OL,10,Fthe Mental Health Act, "following
OL,11,Fattempting entry to (a) neighbour's
OL,12,Fflat resulting in (an) unknown female
OL,13,Fexiting (a) first floor window in fear
OL,14,Fresulting in serious injury requiring
OL,15,Fsurgery".
OL,17,FCalocane, who was a mechanical
OL,18,Fengineering student, had also
OL,19,Fcommitted criminal damage on the day
OL,20,Fof the incident, saying his behaviour
OL,21,Fwas due to workload and exams.
OL,26,@rD@XOUwD@HO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1772132672
OL,3,CUniversity not told of psychiatrist's
OL,4,Cconcerns that Valdo Calocane might kill
OL,6,F"It will not happen again"
OL,8,FThe inquiry was told he was discharged
OL,9,Fon June 17 2020 but re-admitted to
OL,10,Fhospital on July 14, after another
OL,11,Fincident at his accommodation ` with
OL,12,Fhis medical notes on July 16 stating:
OL,13,F"Valdo describes stopping medication
OL,14,Ftwo weeks after discharge from his
OL,15,Flast admission because he read that it
OL,16,Fcould slow the mind.
OL,18,F"(There were) no signs of remorse or
OL,19,Finsight into how his actions have
OL,20,Faffected others.
OL,26,@uD@AOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1772132672
OL,3,CUniversity not told of psychiatrist's
OL,4,Cconcerns that Valdo Calocane might kill
OL,6,F"Dr Seedat (consultant psychiatrist Dr
OL,7,FFaizal Seedat) observed that there
OL,8,Fseems to be no insight or remorse, and
OL,9,Fthat the danger is that it will happen
OL,10,Fagain, and perhaps Valdo will end up
OL,11,Fkilling someone.
OL,13,F"Valdo simply responds by saying it
OL,14,Fwill not happen again. Police are not
OL,15,Fintending to press charges."
OL,17,F"The university are not told"
OL,26,@uD@AOUwD@\O]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1772132672
OL,3,CUniversity not told of psychiatrist's
OL,4,Cconcerns that Valdo Calocane might kill
OL,6,FBarrister Julian Blake, of the
OL,7,Finquiry's team of counsel, said
OL,8,FCalocane had to be held down by other
OL,9,Fresidents during the further incident
OL,10,Fat the student accommodation on July
OL,11,F13 2020.
OL,13,FAfter Ms Thompson confirmed that
OL,14,Finformation from the notes had not
OL,15,Fbeen communicated to the university,
OL,16,FMr Blake asked: "What do you think has
OL,17,Fgone wrong here?
OL,26,@xD@QOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,377,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F376A1772132672
OL,3,CUniversity not told of psychiatrist's
OL,4,Cconcerns that Valdo Calocane might kill
OL,6,F"The consultant psychiatrist said he
OL,7,Fmight end up killing somebody, and the
OL,8,Funiversity are not told that
OL,9,Finformation. Prior to this inquiry,
OL,10,Fwere you aware of that information?"
OL,12,FMs Thompson answered: "I think I only
OL,13,Fbecame aware of it after the incident
OL,14,Fhappened ` after the (2023) attacks.
OL,16,F"We weren't aware of it before then."
OL,18,FSubscribe free to our weekly
